  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm not sure that is a bad thing that the tests won't fail for that case. We will have so many React-wrapping divs in the rendered DOM that users won't be able to target specific elements, unless the one where we specified custom `ais-` classes.\n\nSo letting the test pass if we add our own wrappers or change the inner markup is ok for me, as long as we keep the correct CSS classes on the correct UI elements.\n",
